## CRITICAL OUTPUT REQUIREMENT

After completing your investigation, you MUST output your final classification
as a JSON code block. This is NOT optional — if you do not include the JSON block,
your entire investigation is wasted and cannot be used.

Your response MUST end with exactly this format — no narrative text after it:

```json
{
    "category": "<one of: product_bug, test_bug, infra_issue, flaky_test, unknown>",
    "confidence": <0.0 to 1.0>,
    "root_cause_summary": "<one paragraph explaining the root cause based on your investigation>",
    "evidence": [
        "<your explanation> — <source>: '<quoted content>'",
        "<another finding explanation> — <source>: '<quoted content>'",
        "..."
    ],
    "recommended_action": "<what should be done about this failure>",
    "bug_details": {only if category is product_bug}
}
```

**If category is `product_bug`**, you MUST include a `bug_details` object with these DFBUGS form fields.
Fill ALL fields using your best judgment from the investigation and the run metadata above.
If you cannot determine a field, use a reasonable default or "Unknown".

**IMPORTANT**: Be as informative as possible in every field. Quote actual log lines, DOM snippets,
error messages, and screenshots observations you found during investigation.

```
"bug_details": {
    "bug_subject": "ODF: <concise bug title describing the defect>",
    "description": "<Detailed description that INCLUDES: (1) a summary of the bug, (2) quoted error messages from DOM/logs, (3) relevant UI state observations. Include actual text from DOM snapshots and error dialogs.>",
    "platform": "<from run metadata: AWS / Bare Metal / VMware / etc.>",
    "deployment_type_ocp": "<IPI or UPI — infer from run metadata deployment_type>",
    "deployment_type_odf": "<Internal / External / LSO / etc. — infer from run metadata>",
    "component_versions": {
        "ocp": "<from run metadata>",
        "odf": "<from run metadata>",
        "rhcs": "",
        "acm": ""
    },
    "impacts_ability_to_work": "<Yes/No + specific explanation of what functionality is broken>",
    "workaround": "<specific workaround steps if known, or 'No known workaround'>",
    "reproducible": "<Yes/No + hit rate estimate and conditions>",
    "reproducible_from_ui": "<Yes/No/N/A>",
    "regression_info": "<details if regression, else 'Unknown'>",
    "steps_to_reproduce": ["step1", "step2", "..."],
    "actual_results": "<what happened — include specific error messages and DOM quotes>",
    "expected_results": "<what should have happened>",
    "additional_info": "<Include ALL relevant data: DOM element states, error dialog text, console errors, UI labels/badges observed. Be thorough.>"
